<br>
You can get rid of the banner ads and turn off a lot of the extra toolbars and plugins, but the program is still bloated.  Trillian is a decent replacement, but it's buggy and doesn't support things like single mode message windows that some of us ICQ die hards can't live without. :)<br>
<br>
The good news is, I've hit upon the <b><font size="2">PERFECT</font></b> replacement.<br>
<hr size="1" align="center"><br>
It's called Miranda, and it's a free, GPL'd project to create a very basic replacement ICQ client.  It's fantastic -- small, stable and feature complete as far as all major areas are concerned.  It works beautifully.<br>
<br>
There are screenshots and a FAQ at <a href="http://miranda-icq.sourceforge.net/">miranda-icq.sourceforge.net</a>.  I've also  <a href="http://www.jaddesign.com/download/miranda/">mirrored the files I used</a>.  <br>
<br>
Install <b>miranda0121.exe</b> (the latest official release), and then unzip <b>miranda_nightly.zip</b> (the latest daily build) into the install directory.  If you are so inclined, the other file is a plugin that replicates the "Send Contacts" feature found in ICQ. <p><font face="Verdana" size="1"><b>NIDEN</b><br>Arch Mage of <a href="http://www.unconquered.org/main_page.htm" target="_blank">Unconquered</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub19.ezboard.com/udadiella.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dadiella</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wannabe Unconquered</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(8/6/02 3:56:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub19.ezboard.com/funconqueredfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=271.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Use ICQ?  Read this. :)</span><hr size=1> There's also a great program out that will run all your messengers and IRC in one program. It's called Trillian.  I use it for my ICQ, AIM, and Yahoo.  It seems to be a bit buggy w/ MSN lately. Very easy to use and saves some of the clutter.<br>
